  "text": "The study of abstract convexity began in the early fifties and is extensively studied in van de Vel's monograph [CITATION_1] , where the interval convexity is used for introducing it. The theory of axiomatic convexity is based on just three natural conditions, imposed on a family of subsets of a given set. Definition 1. [CITATION_2] . A family C of subsets of a set X is called a convexity on X if (C1) the empty set ∅ and universal set X are in C;",
